article.headline: Jackson St. 73, Texas Southern 62
article.story: HOUSTON (AP) -- Trey Johnson scored 25 points to help Jackson State to a 73-62 win over Texas Southern on Saturday night. Johnson hit all seven of his free throws and Julius Young, who finished with 14 points, hit all six of his free throws to lead Jackson State (10-8, 4-1 Southwestern Athletic). Garrison Johnson came off the bench to score 12 points and Catraiva Givens added 10 points and seven assists. Texas Southern (7-8, 3-1) had eight more rebounds than Jackson State, but couldn't overcome 11 percent shooting from 3-point range and 25 turnovers. Chris Moore recorded a double-double with 17 points and 13 rebounds. Jacques Jones scored a team-high 25 points and Courtenay Brown added 10. Brown had three blocks and Dominique White added six assists.
